- cs.OH (Optimization and Control) is also a likely category as the paper deals with constrained optimization problems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses randomized search algorithms and benchmarking. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper proposes a benchmarking environment for probabilistic search algorithms, which can be used in machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes a benchmarking environment for search algorithms, which is a subfield of AI.
